[
  {
    "startTime": 15.26,
    "endTime": 18.259,
    "text": "So I begin with an advertisement"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 18.26,
    "endTime": 20.26,
    "text": "inspired by George Orwell"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 20.26,
    "endTime": 23.26,
    "text": "that Apple ran in 1984."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 32.259,
    "endTime": 34.26,
    "text": "(Video) Big Brother: We are one people"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 34.26,
    "endTime": 37.26,
    "text": "with one will, one resolve,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 37.26,
    "endTime": 39.26,
    "text": "one cause."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 39.26,
    "endTime": 42.26,
    "text": "Our enemies shall talk themselves to death,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 42.26,
    "endTime": 45.26,
    "text": "and we will fight them with their own confusion."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 47.26,
    "endTime": 49.26,
    "text": "We shall prevail."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 52.26,
    "endTime": 54.26,
    "text": "Narrator: On January 24th,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 54.26,
    "endTime": 57.26,
    "text": "Apple Computer will introduce Macintosh."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 57.26,
    "endTime": 60.26,
    "text": "And you'll see why 1984"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 60.26,
    "endTime": 62.26,
    "text": "won't be like \"1984.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 62.26,
    "endTime": 65.259,
    "text": "Rebecca MacKinnon: So the underlying message of this video"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 65.26,
    "endTime": 68.26,
    "text": "remains very powerful even today."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 68.26,
    "endTime": 71.26,
    "text": "Technology created by innovative companies"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 71.26,
    "endTime": 74.26,
    "text": "will set us all free."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 74.26,
    "endTime": 77.26,
    "text": "Fast-forward more than two decades:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 77.26,
    "endTime": 80.26,
    "text": "Apple launches the iPhone in China"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 80.26,
    "endTime": 82.26,
    "text": "and censors the Dalai Lama out"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 82.26,
    "endTime": 85.26,
    "text": "along with several other politically sensitive applications"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 85.26,
    "endTime": 87.26,
    "text": "at the request of the Chinese government"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 87.26,
    "endTime": 89.26,
    "text": "for its Chinese app store."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 89.26,
    "endTime": 91.26,
    "text": "The American political cartoonist"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 91.26,
    "endTime": 93.26,
    "text": "Mark Fiore"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 93.26,
    "endTime": 95.26,
    "text": "also had his satire application"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 95.26,
    "endTime": 97.26,
    "text": "censored in the United States"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 97.26,
    "endTime": 99.26,
    "text": "because some of Apple's staff"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 99.26,
    "endTime": 102.26,
    "text": "were concerned it would be offensive to some groups."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 102.26,
    "endTime": 104.26,
    "text": "His app wasn't reinstated"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 104.26,
    "endTime": 107.26,
    "text": "until he won the Pulitzer Prize."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 107.26,
    "endTime": 110.26,
    "text": "The German magazine Stern, a news magazine,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 110.26,
    "endTime": 112.26,
    "text": "had its app censored"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 112.26,
    "endTime": 114.26,
    "text": "because the Apple nannies deemed it"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 114.26,
    "endTime": 117.26,
    "text": "to be a little bit too racy for their users,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 117.26,
    "endTime": 119.26,
    "text": "and despite the fact that this magazine"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 119.26,
    "endTime": 121.26,
    "text": "is perfectly legal for sale"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 121.26,
    "endTime": 124.26,
    "text": "on newsstands throughout Germany."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 124.26,
    "endTime": 126.26,
    "text": "And more controversially, recently,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 126.26,
    "endTime": 129.25900000000001,
    "text": "Apple censored a Palestinian protest app"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 129.259,
    "endTime": 132.26,
    "text": "after the Israeli government voiced concerns"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 132.26,
    "endTime": 135.26,
    "text": "that it might be used to organize violent attacks."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 135.26,
    "endTime": 137.26,
    "text": "So here's the thing."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 137.26,
    "endTime": 139.26,
    "text": "We have a situation where private companies"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 139.26,
    "endTime": 142.26,
    "text": "are applying censorship standards"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 142.26,
    "endTime": 145.26,
    "text": "that are often quite arbitrary"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 145.26,
    "endTime": 147.26,
    "text": "and generally more narrow"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 147.26,
    "endTime": 149.26,
    "text": "than the free speech constitutional standards"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 149.26,
    "endTime": 151.26,
    "text": "that we have in democracies."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 151.26,
    "endTime": 154.26,
    "text": "Or they're responding to censorship requests"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 154.26,
    "endTime": 156.26,
    "text": "by authoritarian regimes"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 156.26,
    "endTime": 158.26,
    "text": "that do not reflect consent of the governed."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 158.26,
    "endTime": 161.26,
    "text": "Or they're responding to requests and concerns"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 161.26,
    "endTime": 165.26,
    "text": "by governments that have no jurisdiction"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 165.26,
    "endTime": 168.26,
    "text": "over many, or most, of the users and viewers"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 168.26,
    "endTime": 171.26,
    "text": "who are interacting with the content in question."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 171.26,
    "endTime": 173.26,
    "text": "So here's the situation."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 173.26,
    "endTime": 175.26,
    "text": "In a pre-Internet world,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 175.26,
    "endTime": 178.26,
    "text": "sovereignty over our physical freedoms,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 178.26,
    "endTime": 180.26,
    "text": "or lack thereof,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 180.26,
    "endTime": 182.26,
    "text": "was controlled almost entirely"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 182.26,
    "endTime": 184.26,
    "text": "by nation-states."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 184.26,
    "endTime": 186.26,
    "text": "But now we have this new layer"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 186.26,
    "endTime": 188.26,
    "text": "of private sovereignty"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 188.26,
    "endTime": 190.26,
    "text": "in cyberspace."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 190.26,
    "endTime": 192.26,
    "text": "And their decisions about software coding,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 192.26,
    "endTime": 195.26,
    "text": "engineering, design, terms of service"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 195.26,
    "endTime": 197.26,
    "text": "all act as a kind of law"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 197.26,
    "endTime": 201.26,
    "text": "that shapes what we can and cannot do with our digital lives."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 201.26,
    "endTime": 203.26,
    "text": "And their sovereignties,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 203.26,
    "endTime": 205.26,
    "text": "cross-cutting, globally interlinked,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 205.26,
    "endTime": 207.26,
    "text": "can in some ways"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 207.26,
    "endTime": 209.26,
    "text": "challenge the sovereignties of nation-states"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 209.26,
    "endTime": 211.26,
    "text": "in very exciting ways,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 211.26,
    "endTime": 213.26,
    "text": "but sometimes also act"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 213.26,
    "endTime": 215.26,
    "text": "to project and extend it"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 215.26,
    "endTime": 217.26,
    "text": "at a time when control"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 217.26,
    "endTime": 219.26,
    "text": "over what people can and cannot do"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 219.26,
    "endTime": 221.26,
    "text": "with information"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 221.26,
    "endTime": 223.26,
    "text": "has more effect than ever"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 223.26,
    "endTime": 225.26,
    "text": "on the exercise of power"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 225.26,
    "endTime": 228.26,
    "text": "in our physical world."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 228.26,
    "endTime": 230.26,
    "text": "After all, even the leader of the free world"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 230.26,
    "endTime": 233.26,
    "text": "needs a little help from the sultan of Facebookistan"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 233.26,
    "endTime": 236.26,
    "text": "if he wants to get reelected next year."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 236.26,
    "endTime": 238.26,
    "text": "And these platforms"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 238.26,
    "endTime": 240.26,
    "text": "were certainly very helpful"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 240.26,
    "endTime": 243.26,
    "text": "to activists in Tunisia and Egypt"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 243.26,
    "endTime": 245.26,
    "text": "this past spring and beyond."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 245.26,
    "endTime": 248.26,
    "text": "As Wael Ghonim,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 248.26,
    "endTime": 251.26,
    "text": "the Google-Egyptian-executive by day,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 251.26,
    "endTime": 253.26,
    "text": "secret-Facebook-activist by night,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 253.26,
    "endTime": 255.26,
    "text": "famously said to CNN"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 255.26,
    "endTime": 257.26,
    "text": "after Mubarak stepped down,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 257.26,
    "endTime": 259.26,
    "text": "\"If you want to liberate a society,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 259.26,
    "endTime": 261.26,
    "text": "just give them the Internet.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 261.26,
    "endTime": 263.26,
    "text": "But overthrowing a government is one thing"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 263.26,
    "endTime": 265.26,
    "text": "and building a stable democracy"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 265.26,
    "endTime": 267.26,
    "text": "is a bit more complicated."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 267.26,
    "endTime": 270.26,
    "text": "On the left there's a photo taken by an Egyptian activist"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 270.26,
    "endTime": 272.26,
    "text": "who was part of the storming"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 272.26,
    "endTime": 275.26,
    "text": "of the Egyptian state security offices in March."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 275.26,
    "endTime": 277.26,
    "text": "And many of the agents"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 277.26,
    "endTime": 279.26,
    "text": "shredded as many of the documents as they could"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 279.26,
    "endTime": 281.26,
    "text": "and left them behind in piles."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 281.26,
    "endTime": 284.26,
    "text": "But some of the files were left behind intact,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 284.26,
    "endTime": 286.26,
    "text": "and activists, some of them,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 286.26,
    "endTime": 289.26,
    "text": "found their own surveillance dossiers"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 289.26,
    "endTime": 292.26,
    "text": "full of transcripts of their email exchanges,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 292.26,
    "endTime": 294.26,
    "text": "their cellphone text message exchanges,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 294.26,
    "endTime": 296.26,
    "text": "even Skype conversations."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 296.26,
    "endTime": 298.26,
    "text": "And one activist actually found"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 298.26,
    "endTime": 301.26,
    "text": "a contract from a Western company"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 301.26,
    "endTime": 303.26,
    "text": "for the sale of surveillance technology"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 303.26,
    "endTime": 305.26,
    "text": "to the Egyptian security forces."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 305.26,
    "endTime": 307.26,
    "text": "And Egyptian activists are assuming"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 307.26,
    "endTime": 309.26,
    "text": "that these technologies for surveillance"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 309.26,
    "endTime": 311.26,
    "text": "are still being used"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 311.26,
    "endTime": 314.26,
    "text": "by the transitional authorities running the networks there."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 315.26,
    "endTime": 318.26,
    "text": "And in Tunisia, censorship actually began to return in May --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 318.26,
    "endTime": 320.26,
    "text": "not nearly as extensively"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 320.26,
    "endTime": 323.26,
    "text": "as under President Ben Ali."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 323.26,
    "endTime": 325.26,
    "text": "But you'll see here a blocked page"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 325.26,
    "endTime": 327.26,
    "text": "of what happens when you try to reach"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 327.26,
    "endTime": 329.26,
    "text": "certain Facebook pages and some other websites"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 329.26,
    "endTime": 331.26,
    "text": "that the transitional authorities"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 331.26,
    "endTime": 334.26,
    "text": "have determined might incite violence."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 334.26,
    "endTime": 336.26,
    "text": "In protest over this,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 336.26,
    "endTime": 338.26,
    "text": "blogger Slim Amamou,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 338.26,
    "endTime": 340.26,
    "text": "who had been jailed under Ben Ali"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 340.26,
    "endTime": 342.26,
    "text": "and then became part of the transitional government"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 342.26,
    "endTime": 344.26,
    "text": "after the revolution,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 344.26,
    "endTime": 347.26,
    "text": "he resigned in protest from the cabinet."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 347.26,
    "endTime": 349.26,
    "text": "But there's been a lot of debate in Tunisia"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 349.26,
    "endTime": 351.26,
    "text": "about how to handle this kind of problem."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 351.26,
    "endTime": 353.26,
    "text": "In fact, on Twitter,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 353.26,
    "endTime": 355.26,
    "text": "there were a number of people who were supportive of the revolution"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 355.26,
    "endTime": 357.26,
    "text": "who said, \"Well actually,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 357.26,
    "endTime": 359.26,
    "text": "we do want democracy and free expression,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 359.26,
    "endTime": 362.26,
    "text": "but there is some kinds of speech that need to be off-bounds"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 362.26,
    "endTime": 365.26,
    "text": "because it's too violent and it might be destabilizing for our democracy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 365.26,
    "endTime": 367.26,
    "text": "But the problem is,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 367.26,
    "endTime": 370.26,
    "text": "how do you decide who is in power to make these decisions"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 370.26,
    "endTime": 372.26,
    "text": "and how do you make sure"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 372.26,
    "endTime": 374.26,
    "text": "that they do not abuse their power?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 374.26,
    "endTime": 376.26,
    "text": "As Riadh Guerfali,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 376.26,
    "endTime": 378.26,
    "text": "the veteran digital activist from Tunisia,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 378.26,
    "endTime": 380.26,
    "text": "remarked over this incident,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 380.26,
    "endTime": 382.26,
    "text": "\"Before, things were simple:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 382.26,
    "endTime": 385.26,
    "text": "you had the good guys on one side and the bad guys on the other."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 385.26,
    "endTime": 388.26,
    "text": "Today, things are a lot more subtle.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 388.26,
    "endTime": 391.26,
    "text": "Welcome to democracy, our Tunisian and Egyptian friends."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 391.26,
    "endTime": 393.26,
    "text": "The reality is"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 393.26,
    "endTime": 396.26,
    "text": "that even in democratic societies today,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 396.26,
    "endTime": 398.26,
    "text": "we do not have good answers"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 398.26,
    "endTime": 400.26,
    "text": "for how you balance the need"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 400.26,
    "endTime": 403.26,
    "text": "for security and law enforcement on one hand"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 403.26,
    "endTime": 405.26,
    "text": "and protection of civil liberties"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 405.26,
    "endTime": 407.26,
    "text": "and free speech on the other"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 407.26,
    "endTime": 409.26,
    "text": "in our digital networks."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 409.26,
    "endTime": 411.26,
    "text": "In fact, in the United States,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 411.26,
    "endTime": 414.26,
    "text": "whatever you may think of Julian Assange,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 414.26,
    "endTime": 417.26,
    "text": "even people who are not necessarily big fans of his"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 417.26,
    "endTime": 419.26,
    "text": "are very concerned about the way"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 419.26,
    "endTime": 422.26,
    "text": "in which the United States government and some companies have handled Wikileaks."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 422.26,
    "endTime": 425.26,
    "text": "Amazon webhosting dropped Wikileaks as a customer"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 425.26,
    "endTime": 429.26,
    "text": "after receiving a complaint from U.S. Senator Joe Lieberman,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 429.26,
    "endTime": 431.26,
    "text": "despite the fact"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 431.26,
    "endTime": 433.26,
    "text": "that Wikileaks had not been charged,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 433.26,
    "endTime": 435.26,
    "text": "let alone convicted,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 435.26,
    "endTime": 438.26,
    "text": "of any crime."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 438.26,
    "endTime": 440.26,
    "text": "So we assume"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 440.26,
    "endTime": 443.26,
    "text": "that the Internet is a border-busting technology."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 443.26,
    "endTime": 446.26,
    "text": "This is a map of social networks worldwide,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 446.26,
    "endTime": 449.26,
    "text": "and certainly Facebook has conquered much of the world --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 449.26,
    "endTime": 451.26,
    "text": "which is either a good or a bad thing,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 451.26,
    "endTime": 453.26,
    "text": "depending on how you like"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 453.26,
    "endTime": 455.26,
    "text": "the way Facebook manages its service."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 455.26,
    "endTime": 457.26,
    "text": "But borders do persist"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 457.26,
    "endTime": 459.26,
    "text": "in some parts of cyberspace."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 459.26,
    "endTime": 461.26,
    "text": "In Brazil and Japan,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 461.26,
    "endTime": 464.26,
    "text": "it's for unique cultural and linguistic reasons."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 464.26,
    "endTime": 466.26,
    "text": "But if you look at China, Vietnam"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 466.26,
    "endTime": 469.26,
    "text": "and a number of the former Soviet states,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 469.26,
    "endTime": 471.26,
    "text": "what's happening there is more troubling."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 471.26,
    "endTime": 473.26,
    "text": "You have a situation"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 473.26,
    "endTime": 475.26,
    "text": "where the relationship between government"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 475.26,
    "endTime": 478.26,
    "text": "and local social networking companies"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 478.26,
    "endTime": 480.26,
    "text": "is creating a situation"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 480.26,
    "endTime": 482.26,
    "text": "where, effectively,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 482.26,
    "endTime": 485.26,
    "text": "the empowering potential of these platforms"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 485.26,
    "endTime": 487.26,
    "text": "is being constrained"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 487.26,
    "endTime": 489.26,
    "text": "because of these relationships"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 489.26,
    "endTime": 491.26,
    "text": "between companies and government."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 491.26,
    "endTime": 493.26,
    "text": "Now in China,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 493.26,
    "endTime": 495.26,
    "text": "you have the \"great firewall,\" as it's well-known,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 495.26,
    "endTime": 497.26,
    "text": "that blocks Facebook"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 497.26,
    "endTime": 500.26,
    "text": "and Twitter and now Google+"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 500.26,
    "endTime": 503.26,
    "text": "and many of the other overseas websites."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 503.26,
    "endTime": 506.26,
    "text": "And that's done in part with the help from Western technology."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 506.26,
    "endTime": 509.26,
    "text": "But that's only half of the story."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 509.26,
    "endTime": 511.26,
    "text": "The other part of the story"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 511.26,
    "endTime": 514.26,
    "text": "are requirements that the Chinese government places"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 514.26,
    "endTime": 517.26,
    "text": "on all companies operating on the Chinese Internet,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 517.26,
    "endTime": 519.26,
    "text": "known as a system of self-discipline."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 519.26,
    "endTime": 522.26,
    "text": "In plain English, that means censorship and surveillance"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 522.26,
    "endTime": 524.26,
    "text": "of their users."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 524.26,
    "endTime": 527.26,
    "text": "And this is a ceremony I actually attended in 2009"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 527.26,
    "endTime": 530.26,
    "text": "where the Internet Society of China presented awards"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 530.26,
    "endTime": 533.26,
    "text": "to the top 20 Chinese companies"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 533.26,
    "endTime": 536.26,
    "text": "that are best at exercising self-discipline --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 536.26,
    "endTime": 538.26,
    "text": "i.e. policing their content."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 538.26,
    "endTime": 541.26,
    "text": "And Robin Li, CEO of Baidu,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 541.26,
    "endTime": 543.26,
    "text": "China's dominant search engine,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 543.26,
    "endTime": 546.26,
    "text": "was one of the recipients."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 546.26,
    "endTime": 550.26,
    "text": "In Russia, they do not generally block the Internet"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 550.26,
    "endTime": 552.26,
    "text": "and directly censor websites."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 552.26,
    "endTime": 554.26,
    "text": "But this is a website called Rospil"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 554.26,
    "endTime": 556.26,
    "text": "that's an anti-corruption site."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 556.26,
    "endTime": 558.26,
    "text": "And earlier this year,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 558.26,
    "endTime": 560.26,
    "text": "there was a troubling incident"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 560.26,
    "endTime": 563.26,
    "text": "where people who had made donations to Rospil"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 563.26,
    "endTime": 565.26,
    "text": "through a payments processing system"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 565.26,
    "endTime": 567.26,
    "text": "called Yandex Money"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 567.26,
    "endTime": 569.26,
    "text": "suddenly received threatening phone calls"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 569.26,
    "endTime": 572.26,
    "text": "from members of a nationalist party"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 572.26,
    "endTime": 574.26,
    "text": "who had obtained details"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 574.26,
    "endTime": 577.26,
    "text": "about donors to Rospil"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 577.26,
    "endTime": 579.26,
    "text": "through members of the security services"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 579.26,
    "endTime": 582.26,
    "text": "who had somehow obtained this information"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 582.26,
    "endTime": 585.26,
    "text": "from people at Yandex Money."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 585.26,
    "endTime": 587.26,
    "text": "This has a chilling effect"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 587.26,
    "endTime": 589.26,
    "text": "on people's ability to use the Internet"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 589.26,
    "endTime": 592.26,
    "text": "to hold government accountable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 592.26,
    "endTime": 594.26,
    "text": "So we have a situation in the world today"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 594.26,
    "endTime": 596.26,
    "text": "where in more and more countries"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 596.26,
    "endTime": 599.26,
    "text": "the relationship between citizens and governments"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 599.26,
    "endTime": 602.26,
    "text": "is mediated through the Internet,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 602.26,
    "endTime": 604.26,
    "text": "which is comprised primarily"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 604.26,
    "endTime": 608.26,
    "text": "of privately owned and operated services."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 608.26,
    "endTime": 610.26,
    "text": "So the important question, I think,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 610.26,
    "endTime": 612.26,
    "text": "is not this debate over whether the Internet"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 612.26,
    "endTime": 615.26,
    "text": "is going to help the good guys more than the bad guys."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 615.26,
    "endTime": 617.26,
    "text": "Of course, it's going to empower"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 617.26,
    "endTime": 620.26,
    "text": "whoever is most skilled at using the technology"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 620.26,
    "endTime": 622.26,
    "text": "and best understands the Internet"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 622.26,
    "endTime": 625.26,
    "text": "in comparison with whoever their adversary is."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 625.26,
    "endTime": 628.26,
    "text": "The most urgent question we need to be asking today"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 628.26,
    "endTime": 630.26,
    "text": "is how do we make sure"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 630.26,
    "endTime": 632.26,
    "text": "that the Internet evolves"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 632.26,
    "endTime": 635.26,
    "text": "in a citizen-centric manner."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 635.26,
    "endTime": 637.26,
    "text": "Because I think all of you will agree"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 637.26,
    "endTime": 640.26,
    "text": "that the only legitimate purpose of government"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 640.26,
    "endTime": 642.26,
    "text": "is to serve citizens,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 642.26,
    "endTime": 644.26,
    "text": "and I would argue"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 644.26,
    "endTime": 646.26,
    "text": "that the only legitimate purpose of technology"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 646.26,
    "endTime": 648.26,
    "text": "is to improve our lives,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 648.26,
    "endTime": 652.26,
    "text": "not to manipulate or enslave us."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 653.26,
    "endTime": 655.26,
    "text": "So the question is,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 655.26,
    "endTime": 657.26,
    "text": "we know how to hold government accountable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 657.26,
    "endTime": 659.26,
    "text": "We don't necessarily always do it very well,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 659.26,
    "endTime": 662.26,
    "text": "but we have a sense of what the models are,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 662.26,
    "endTime": 664.26,
    "text": "politically and institutionally, to do that."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 664.26,
    "endTime": 666.26,
    "text": "How do you hold the sovereigns of cyberspace"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 666.26,
    "endTime": 668.26,
    "text": "accountable to the public interest"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 668.26,
    "endTime": 670.26,
    "text": "when most CEO's argue"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 670.26,
    "endTime": 672.26,
    "text": "that their main obligation"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 672.26,
    "endTime": 674.26,
    "text": "is to maximize shareholder profit?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 674.26,
    "endTime": 676.26,
    "text": "And government regulation"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 676.26,
    "endTime": 678.26,
    "text": "often isn't helping all that much."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 678.26,
    "endTime": 680.26,
    "text": "You have situations, for instance, in France"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 680.26,
    "endTime": 682.26,
    "text": "where president Sarkozy"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 682.26,
    "endTime": 684.26,
    "text": "tells the CEO's of Internet companies,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 684.26,
    "endTime": 686.26,
    "text": "\"We're the only legitimate representatives"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 686.26,
    "endTime": 688.26,
    "text": "of the public interest.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 688.26,
    "endTime": 690.26,
    "text": "But then he goes and champions laws"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 690.26,
    "endTime": 692.26,
    "text": "like the infamous \"three-strikes\" law"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 692.26,
    "endTime": 694.26,
    "text": "that would disconnect citizens from the Internet"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 694.26,
    "endTime": 696.26,
    "text": "for file sharing,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 696.26,
    "endTime": 699.26,
    "text": "which has been condemned by the U.N. Special Rapporteur"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 699.26,
    "endTime": 701.26,
    "text": "on Freedom of Expression"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 701.26,
    "endTime": 704.26,
    "text": "as being a disproportionate violation"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 704.26,
    "endTime": 706.26,
    "text": "of citizens' right to communications,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 706.26,
    "endTime": 709.26,
    "text": "and has raised questions amongst civil society groups"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 709.26,
    "endTime": 711.26,
    "text": "about whether"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 711.26,
    "endTime": 713.26,
    "text": "some political representatives"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 713.26,
    "endTime": 715.26,
    "text": "are more interested in preserving"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 715.26,
    "endTime": 718.26,
    "text": "the interests of the entertainment industry"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 718.26,
    "endTime": 720.26,
    "text": "than they are in defending the rights of their citizens."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 720.26,
    "endTime": 722.26,
    "text": "And here in the United Kingdom"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 722.26,
    "endTime": 724.26,
    "text": "there's also concern over"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 724.26,
    "endTime": 726.26,
    "text": "a law called the Digital Economy Act"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 726.26,
    "endTime": 728.26,
    "text": "that's placing more onus"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 728.26,
    "endTime": 730.26,
    "text": "on private intermediaries"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 730.26,
    "endTime": 734.26,
    "text": "to police citizen behavior."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 734.26,
    "endTime": 736.26,
    "text": "So what we need to recognize"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 736.26,
    "endTime": 738.26,
    "text": "is that if we want to have"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 738.26,
    "endTime": 741.26,
    "text": "a citizen-centric Internet in the future,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 741.26,
    "endTime": 743.26,
    "text": "we need a broader and more sustained"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 743.26,
    "endTime": 745.26,
    "text": "Internet freedom movement."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 745.26,
    "endTime": 748.26,
    "text": "After all, companies didn't stop polluting groundwater"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 748.26,
    "endTime": 751.26,
    "text": "as a matter of course,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 751.26,
    "endTime": 753.26,
    "text": "or employing 10-year-olds as a matter of course,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 753.26,
    "endTime": 755.26,
    "text": "just because executives woke up one day"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 755.26,
    "endTime": 758.26,
    "text": "and decided it was the right thing to do."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 758.26,
    "endTime": 760.26,
    "text": "It was the result of decades of sustained activism,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 760.26,
    "endTime": 762.26,
    "text": "shareholder advocacy"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 762.26,
    "endTime": 764.26,
    "text": "and consumer advocacy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 764.26,
    "endTime": 768.26,
    "text": "Similarly, governments don't enact"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 768.26,
    "endTime": 771.26,
    "text": "intelligent environmental and labor laws"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 771.26,
    "endTime": 774.26,
    "text": "just because politicians wake up one day."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 774.26,
    "endTime": 776.26,
    "text": "It's the result of very sustained and prolonged"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 776.26,
    "endTime": 778.26,
    "text": "political activism"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 778.26,
    "endTime": 780.26,
    "text": "that you get the right regulations,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 780.26,
    "endTime": 782.26,
    "text": "and that you get the right corporate behavior."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 782.26,
    "endTime": 784.26,
    "text": "We need to make the same approach"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 784.26,
    "endTime": 786.26,
    "text": "with the Internet."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 786.26,
    "endTime": 788.26,
    "text": "We also are going to need"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 788.26,
    "endTime": 790.26,
    "text": "political innovation."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 790.26,
    "endTime": 793.26,
    "text": "Eight hundred years ago, approximately,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 793.26,
    "endTime": 795.26,
    "text": "the barons of England decided"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 795.26,
    "endTime": 797.26,
    "text": "that the Divine Right of Kings"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 797.26,
    "endTime": 800.26,
    "text": "was no longer working for them so well,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 800.26,
    "endTime": 802.26,
    "text": "and they forced King John"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 802.26,
    "endTime": 805.26,
    "text": "to sign the Magna Carta,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 805.26,
    "endTime": 807.26,
    "text": "which recognized"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 807.26,
    "endTime": 809.26,
    "text": "that even the king"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 809.26,
    "endTime": 812.26,
    "text": "who claimed to have divine rule"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 812.26,
    "endTime": 815.26,
    "text": "still had to abide by a basic set of rules."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 815.26,
    "endTime": 818.26,
    "text": "This set off a cycle"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 818.26,
    "endTime": 820.26,
    "text": "of what we can call political innovation,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 820.26,
    "endTime": 823.26,
    "text": "which led eventually to the idea of consent of the governed --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 823.26,
    "endTime": 826.26,
    "text": "which was implemented for the first time"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 826.26,
    "endTime": 829.26,
    "text": "by that radical revolutionary government"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 829.26,
    "endTime": 832.26,
    "text": "in America across the pond."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 832.26,
    "endTime": 835.26,
    "text": "So now we need to figure out"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 835.26,
    "endTime": 837.26,
    "text": "how to build consent of the networked."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 837.26,
    "endTime": 839.26,
    "text": "And what does that look like?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 839.26,
    "endTime": 842.26,
    "text": "At the moment, we still don't know."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 842.26,
    "endTime": 846.26,
    "text": "But it's going to require innovation"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 846.26,
    "endTime": 849.26,
    "text": "that's not only going to need"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 849.26,
    "endTime": 851.26,
    "text": "to focus on politics,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 851.26,
    "endTime": 853.26,
    "text": "on geopolitics,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 853.26,
    "endTime": 855.26,
    "text": "but it's also going to need"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 855.26,
    "endTime": 858.26,
    "text": "to deal with questions"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 858.26,
    "endTime": 861.26,
    "text": "of business management, investor behavior,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 861.26,
    "endTime": 863.26,
    "text": "consumer choice"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 863.26,
    "endTime": 867.26,
    "text": "and even software design and engineering."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 867.26,
    "endTime": 870.26,
    "text": "Each and every one of us has a vital part to play"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 870.26,
    "endTime": 873.26,
    "text": "in building the kind of world"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 873.26,
    "endTime": 876.26,
    "text": "in which government and technology"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 876.26,
    "endTime": 879.26,
    "text": "serve the world's people and not the other way around."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 879.26,
    "endTime": 881.26,
    "text": "Thank you very much."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 881.26,
    "endTime": 886.26,
    "text": "(Applause)"
  }
]